title: Outages, downed trees, other damage reported around First Coast | firstcoastnews.com
text: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. â€” The Severe Thunderstorm Watch several counties on the First Coast were under Friday morning, [has been cancelled](https://www.facebook.com/groups/159442124973593/?hoisted_section_header_type=recently_seen&multi_permalinks=1177346926516436). First Coast News has crews out assessing storm damage; click [here](/video/news/live_breaking/live-radar-another-batch-of-severe-weather-rolling-across-first-coast/77-c3b05cce-cb8c-4deb-a490-b5d0865fb48c) to watch a live radar of how severe weather is rolling across the area. Here are damage reports county-by county. Columbia County Trees and power lines are down, according to Columbia County Emergency Management Director Shayne Morgan. There are also widespread power outages, to include the following companies: - Duke Energy - Suwannee Valley Electric - Clay Electric - Florida Power & Light Baker County There have been reports of tree limbs down and shingles blown off roofs. Duval County Widespread power outages have happened across the county. Big Oak trees are down near 'The Pig Bar-B-Q' restaurant on Lem Turner Road. Multiple trees are also down on houses along Trout River Boulevard. Power lines are down on Eastport Road and a tree fell on top of them. Duval County Public Schools [posted on Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/duvalschools#?jfe) that "many" schools are experiencing weather-related power and telephone outages. A semi-truck was overturned on the Dames Point Bridge after wind speeds topped 73 mph in Jacksonville. The Jacksonville Fire and Rescue Department says one person was taken to a local hospital with non-life-threatening injuries. Clay County There are widespread power outages and several downed trees off of Springfield Road, according to Emergency Management Director Timothy Devin.
